 of high-degree shocked ordinary chondrites\nrequires strong collision events (impact velocities above 8 km/s and/or large\nsizes of impactors). A large amount of asteroid material escapes during an\nimpact event (up to 90%); however, only a small portion of the escaping\nmaterial is shock-darkened (6%).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 23 Aug 2022 14:39:43 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-08-24"}
